main event: A ground radar observation recorded a round object near Lake, Florida, believed to be a satellite.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 20 minutes,The object was described as a point source of light similar to a star,The ground visual observation showed the object moving straight across the sky,The sighting was reported at an azimuth of 270 degrees and elevation of 60 degrees,The conclusion indicated the object was probably an Earth satellite in orbit.
sighted object: one round object, point source of light
witness description: civilian engineer from Sugarland Ave., Orlando, Florida
